g.text: Learn to create and open-source an interactive quiz app with Python!
Check out the project at: https://github.com/pwenker/quizli/
--install-completion Install completion for the current shell.
--show-completion Show completion for the current shell, to copy it or
demo Open the documentation page in the browser
start Start the quiz with the configuration of your choice.
Open the documentation page in the browser
Start the quiz with the configuration of your choice.
There are 2 ways to create a quiz with `quizli`:
1. From a csv file containing question-answer pairs: e.g. `quizli start
--from-csv examples/quiz.csv` 2. From a function in the `example` module:
- Shuffle the quiz with the `--randomize` flag (default), or keep it
- Terminate the quiz with the first wrong answer with `mode=sudden_death`,
--from-csv PATH Read a quiz from a csv-file
--mode [sudden_death|complete] Select the condition for the quiz to end
--randomize / --in-order Shuffle the quiz before starting it
